      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add Authorization header to provider preflight probe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCron job preflight check (GET {baseUrl}/models) was missing auth or using wrong auth for local provider probes. Fixed credential resolution path, error redaction, CI compilation errors, and custom-header auth double-Bearer issue.\n\n## Changes\n\n### P0: Error Redaction — Prevent auth secret leakage\n- **model-preflight.runtime.ts**: Replaced String(params.error) with \formatErrorMessage() — the shared redacting formatter that masks Bearer tokens, API keys, and other credentials before they appear in cron preflight logs or delivery payloads.\n\n### P0.5: AgentDir/WorkspaceDir Type Contract — Fix TS compilation\n- **model-preflight.runtime.ts**: Added ^GgentDir?: string; workspaceDir?: string; to preflightCronModelProvider's parameter type\n- **\run.ts**: Passes actual ^GgentDir and workspaceDir values from PreparedCronRunContext into preflight call\n- **Fixes 3 CI failures** (checks-node-compact-small-3, check-prod-types, check-test-types) — all failing with TS2339 on these missing props\n\n### P1: Custom-header auth precedence — No double auth\n- **Bug**: When \request.auth.mode: \"header\" configured a custom auth header, preflight still called \resolveApiKeyForProvider() to inject Authorization: Bearer — sending both custom header AND Bearer (double auth)\n- **Fix**: Added guard providerConfig?.request?.auth?.mode !== \"header\" on line 259 to skip fallthrough to \resolveApiKeyForProvider when header mode has a valid custom auth header\n- **Matches provider-request-config.ts contract**: header mode suppresses Bearer injection (normal request path already follows this rule)\n- Covers both custom headerName and custom-prefixed Authorization header scenarios\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Cron job preflight GET /models to local provider was sending no Authorization header (original bug), and after the initial attempt lacked full credential chain resolution, had no custom-header auth support, leaked auth secrets in error logs, failed TS compilation, and sent double auth (custom header + Bearer) when header mode was configured.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\n- **OS:** Ubuntu 24.04 (Oracle VPS)\n- **Runtime:** Node.js v24.15.0\n- **OpenClaw version:** 2026.5.18 (npm install)\n- **Provider:** LiteLLM proxy at http://127.0.0.1:4000\n- **Auth method:** LITELLM_API_KEY environment variable\n\n**Evidence after fix:** LiteLLM proxy logs before (top) and after (bottom) the patch show GET /models now gets 200 OK instead of 401:\n\n![Before/after terminal comparison](https://github.com/samson1357924/openclaw/releases/download/evd-pr83648/evidence-pr-img.jpg)\n\nBefore — no auth header, cron preflight triggers 401:\n\\\\\text\n17:30:05 LiteLLM Proxy:ERROR - Exception occured - No api key passed in.\nRequester IP Address:127.0.0.1\n127.0.0.1:58244 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 401 Unauthorized\n127.0.0.1:50768 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n\\\\\n\nAfter — auth header sent, preflight succeeds:\n\\\\\text\n127.0.0.1:45914 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n127.0.0.1:49934 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n\\\\\n\n**Observed result after fix:** GET /models response changed from 401 Unauthorized to 200 OK. No more \"No api key passed in\" errors. Cron preflight cache populates correctly. All existing tests pass (23 tests, 0 failures). Header mode custom auth no longer sends redundant Bearer token.\n\n**Verification:**\n- ✅ 23 tests pass (13 original + 10 new for header-mode auth and double-Bearer prevention)\n- ✅ 3 CI compilation errors fixed (TS2339 on agentDir/workspaceDir)\n- ✅ Code reviewer: APPROVE (zero critical issues)\n- ✅ Test engineer: 23/23 pass, P1 scenario directly verified\n- ✅ Security: Auth secrets redacted in error messages via shared redacting formatter\n- ✅ Feature: Both authorization-bearer and header auth modes supported, no double auth\n\n## Files Changed\n\n- src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.ts — auth resolution, error redaction, header-mode support, double-Bearer prevention\n- src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts — wire agentDir/workspaceDir to preflight\n- src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts — 23 tests (13 original + 10 new)\n\nCloses #83648\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-preflight-clean",
